articles.title: Aryna Sabalenka beats Jessica Pegula to win her first US Open - NPR
articles.description: Aryna Sabalenka of Belarus got past American Jessica Pegula to win her first U.S. Open women’s title and third career Grand Slam title.
articles.content:
NEW YORK Aryna Sabalenka got past Jessica Pegula 7-5, 7-5 in a rollicking U.S. Open womens final Saturday to win her first championship at Flushing Meadows and third Grand Slam title of her career.
